            <thetext>Experiment with Object disposing (array slicing, etc.)

Array slicing to remove data also reduces memory usage of Internet Explorer. When disposing objects and not leaving the page the IE will not collect garbage, so that even disposed objects are not freed from memory. For a long-time running application this would mean an increase of memory over the runtime. This is not directly a memory leak, as the browser will freed memory after leaving the page completely.</thetext>
